# Custom Git Secrets Rules
# 
# Add your own regex patterns here to detect additional secrets
# Each line should be a valid regex pattern
# 
# Example patterns:
# my-company-api-key-[0-9a-zA-Z]{32}
# internal-token:\s*.+
# project-specific-secret=.+
#
# To activate these rules:
# 1. Copy this file to custom-rules.txt (remove .example)
# 2. Add your patterns (one per line)
# 3. The wrapper script will automatically load them
#
# Uncomment and modify the examples below, or add your own:

# Example: Detect specific API key format
# mycompany_[0-9a-zA-Z]{40}

# Example: Detect database connection strings with passwords
# mysql://.*:.*@.*

# Example: Detect internal secret environment variables
# INTERNAL_SECRET_KEY\s*=\s*.+
